<HEAD>Government Easing Some Requirements For Delinquent Borrowers</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DON KENDALL</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Farm Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Under pressure from <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> Farmers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Home </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Administration </ORGANIZATION> is easing some of the paperwork requirements for delinquent borrowers. But it says a 45-day deadline for responding to overdue notices wo n't change. A growing number of lawmakers have been urging the <ORGANIZATION> Agriculture </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> agency to extend the deadline, which gives farmers 45 days in which to respond after receiving official notices to begin settling overdue loan accounts. The notices were sent out last month to more than 80,000 delinquent borrowers who owe FmHA more than $ 8 billion. `` There's just no way legally we can stretch it -LRB- the deadline -RRB-,'' acting agency Administrator <PERSON> La </PERSON> <PERSON> Verne </PERSON> <PERSON> Ausman </PERSON> said Friday. `` We must hear from the farmer within that time.'' Several basic `` response'' forms must be completed and returned within 45 days as the minimum requirement. <PERSON> Ausman </PERSON> said that in order to ease paperwork requirements for late repayers, <ORGANIZATION> FmHA </ORGANIZATION> county offices will accept supporting documents for the applications after the 45-day deadline, but that such agreements must be worked out with those offices. The notices were sent out to FmHA borrowers who were at least 180 days delinquent in repaying loans. The notices informed them of loan servicing and restructuring options, and said failure to respond would trigger `` acceleration'' of loan collection, a step toward foreclosure or forced sale of assets. `` We have advised our field offices to use a test of reasonableness with borrowers who, through no fault of their own, are unable to complete all the forms on time,'' <PERSON> Ausman </PERSON> said. `` For example,'' he added, `` if because of illness or other circumstances beyond his or her control, a farmer could n't obtain all the information he or she needed, we wo n't be hard-nosed if they have given us completed response forms, and farm and home plans. But we will be looking for evidence of a good-faith effort on the part of the borrower to get all the forms in a timely manner.'' <PERSON> Ausman </PERSON> said that as a minimum, the documents that must be sent in within 45 days include: _ Form FmHA 410-1, Application for <ORGANIZATION> FmHA </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION> _ Form FmHA 431-2, Farm and Home Plan, including the balance sheet _ Attachment 2, Acknowledgement of Notice of Program Availability, or Attachment 4, Response to Notice Informing Me of <ORGANIZATION> FmHA </ORGANIZATION>'s Intent to Accelerate My Loan
