<HEAD>On the Light Side</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROCKVILLE, Md. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Drivers who overstayed their parking meters received a surprise holiday message _ in meter _ from <LOCATION> Montgomery </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION>. Parking employees in the county north of <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> D.C. </LOCATION>, put a few lines of poetry on the windshields of violators Thursday instead of the usual $ 10 tickets. The 4-by-8 inch cards bore this greeting: `` The meter was red as time had expired `` In the rush of the season we knew you'd be tired, `` A parking ticket would just make you blue `` In the holiday spirit this just would n't do, `` So during this time of friendship and good cheer `` Season's Greetings to you and best wishes all year.'' The holiday gesture cost the county approximately $ 10,000 in potential fines, officials said.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>TEMPLE CITY, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 For 56 years, <PERSON> Betty </PERSON> <PERSON> Sedat </PERSON> and <PERSON> Grace </PERSON> <PERSON> Dutton </PERSON> have been exchanging Christmas cards _ or rather one Christmas card, sent back and forth year after year. The greeting features a bagpipe-playing Scotsman with the verse: `` Hoot! for a Jolly Christmas! I'll send a card to wish ye a Christmas full of cheer. I'll send my name in pencil so ye'll use the card next year.'' Mrs. <PERSON> Sedat </PERSON> first sent the card to her friend in 1932. `` I thought it was funny,'' she said. `` So I did sign it in pencil along with the date, mailed it off to <PERSON> Grace </PERSON>, and forgot all about it.'' Sure enough, a year later it returned with Ms. <PERSON> Dutton </PERSON>'s name signed below Mrs. <PERSON> Sedat </PERSON>'s. `` We signed and dated it every year, in pencil of course, first on the front, then on the back, until we ran out of room,'' Mrs. <PERSON> Sedat </PERSON> said. The exchange continued even after Mrs. <PERSON> Sedat </PERSON> moved to <LOCATION> Guatemala </LOCATION> with her husband to do missionary work for several years with the <ORGANIZATION> Nazarene </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Church </ORGANIZATION>. The friends say their relationship has been as durable as the card. `` We keep in touch, and see each other several times a year,'' said Mrs. <PERSON> Sedat </PERSON>.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 For those who are n't resolving to tighten their budgets for the new year, a <LOCATION> Boston </LOCATION> hotel is offering `` total indulgence'' for `` as long as you want it or can afford it'' _ at a mere $ 3,000 per night. Beginning Jan. 3, the <ORGANIZATION> Boston </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ritz-Carlton </ORGANIZATION> will join with the new $ 2 million Spa at The <ORGANIZATION> Heritage </ORGANIZATION> a block away to offer guests a night of `` unparalleled, unremitted pampering,'' according to the hotel's promotional literature The $ 3,000-per-couple package _ tax and tips included _ offers limousine pick-up, a night in the posh hotel's Presidential Suite, unlimited food and drink and `` all the spa services that two people can indulge in individually or collectively.'' Spa guests may attend an exercise class, use the health club's weightlifting and cardiovascular equipment, or swim in a four-lane pool that features `` artistic falling leaves across the bottom in colorful tiles. Next is an hour of massage _ Swedish, polarity, cross fiber, sports or shiatsu _ or a choice of herbal steam wraps, Austrian mud body treatment, seaweed body wrap, cellulite treatment, clay body wrap, brush and tone treatment, or a Swiss shower. The package also includes a detailed fitness evaluation and nutrition advice, a facial, blow-dry and, for women, make-up consultation and application. In addition to its classic French cuisine, the hotel also offers low-calorie, low-cholesterol and low-sodium dishes.
