<DATELINE>FRESNO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Her home was gutted by a fire blamed on a short in Christmas tree lights, but <PERSON> Diana </PERSON> <PERSON> Bojorquez </PERSON> said the holiday has been salvaged by the generosity of others. Even as the fire burned Thursday morning, people began offering help, Ms. <PERSON> Bojorquez </PERSON> said Friday. `` Maybe it's because it's the Christmas season,'' she said. `` It started when we were standing outside watching our home burn. People gave us clothing and my daughter a pair of shoes right there. A collection among city workers in this community 200 miles north of <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> produced $ 575 in cash, furniture and a 15-pound Christmas turkey for Ms. <PERSON> Bojorquez </PERSON> and her 7-year-old daughter, <PERSON> Adrienne </PERSON>. `` It's going to be a nice Christmas after all,'' Ms. <PERSON> Bojorquez </PERSON> said.
