<HEAD>Wheelchair Arrives For Mother Of Disabled Boy</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Spelling and grammatical errors in 4th graf are John's.</NOTE>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto upcoming</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Christmas came early this year for a disabled boy who told Santa the only gift he wanted was a wheelchair for his mom. A motorized wheelchair arrived Friday from <LOCATION> Buffalo </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.Y. </LOCATION>, for <PERSON> Victoria </PERSON> <PERSON> Coslett </PERSON>, 39. Weeks ago, it appeared that Ms. <PERSON> Coslett </PERSON> and her 10-year-old son, <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Wonggoun </PERSON>, would not celebrate Christmas. With his mother confined to their apartment and unable to maneuver her old wheelchair outdoors to watch him play, <PERSON> Wonggoun </PERSON> wrapped empty boxes to place under the sparsely decorated Christmas tree, then sat down and wrote <LOCATION> Santa </LOCATION>. His letter said: `` The only gift i would like is an elecric wheelchair for my mom. She ca n't walk and her hands are to weak for the one welfair gave her 2 years ago. I would love to see her outside without help and watch me play. Can you help me with my wish?'' The note made it as far as the <LOCATION> U.S </LOCATION>. Postal Service in <LOCATION> Palm </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Springs </LOCATION>, where <PERSON> Denise </PERSON> <PERSON> Reusche </PERSON>, a clerk, opened the letter. Each year, the post office in the desert resort processes about 1,000 letters to <LOCATION> Santa </LOCATION>. Workers usually send a letter in return. But when Ms. <PERSON> Reusche </PERSON> read <PERSON> John </PERSON>'s letter, she decided to contact <ORGANIZATION> Fortress </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Scientific </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, a <LOCATION> Buffalo </LOCATION> wheelchair manufacturer, which shipped the gift. Ms. <PERSON> Coslett </PERSON> and <PERSON> John </PERSON> were injured in a 1981 traffic crash. She was left with ruptured spinal discs. <PERSON> John </PERSON> was partially brain damaged and suffers recurring seizures and memory lapses. He also has juvenile arthritis.
